@FeignClient(name = "inventory-service", fallback = InventoryFallback.class)
public interface InventoryClient {
    @GetMapping("/api/inventory/{productId}")
    InventoryDto getInventory(@PathVariable String productId);
}

@Component
public class InventoryFallback implements InventoryClient {
    @Override
    public InventoryDto getInventory(String productId) {
        return new InventoryDto(productId, 0, false); // assume out of stock
    }
}

@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired InventoryClient inventory;
    public Order create(OrderRequest req) {
        InventoryDto inv = inventory.getInventory(req.getProductId()); // auto load-balanced
        if (!inv.isAvailable()) throw new OutOfStockException();
        ...
    }
}
```

**Key insight:** Feign generates HTTP client from interface. With Eureka/LoadBalancer, client-side load balancing is automatic. Fallback handles service unavailability.

